The room lay bare and quiet before Cody. He moved from the entrance toward a door to his right, just in time to avoid Lulu
as she barreled into the room. A fierce light glowed in the Pekingese's eyes, and he thought he saw a trace of fresh blood on
her muzzle. "Best not to investigate too closely," Cody said to himself, resigned. "Whether it was friend or foe, it's
neither anymore."
